      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and dice your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in water (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720446773476-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720446773476-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720446773476-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720446773476-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720446773476-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick and with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>diced sweet potato</strong> to the pan and cook for 5 min for until lightly browned</p><p>Once lightly browned, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720446776927-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720446776927-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720446776927-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720446776927-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720446776927-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>half your</strong> <strong>curry powder</strong> and mix everything together</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>with<strong> </strong>350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and keep covered until later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720446780305-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720446780305-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720446780305-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720446780305-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720446780305-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat the grill to medium-high</p><p>Chop your <strong>free range chicken thighs</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>mango chutney</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720446790034-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720446790034-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720446790034-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720446790034-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720446790034-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Thread the <strong>marinated chicken</strong> onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong> and add them to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to the<strong> chicken skewers</strong> and put the tray under the grill for 10-12 min, turning once halfway, or until slightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>mango chicken skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720446793920-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720446793920-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720446793920-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720446793920-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720446793920-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a bowl with your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> coriander yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720446800034-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720446800034-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720446800034-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720446800034-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720446800034-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and chop finely</p><p>Once the mango chicken skewers are almost ready, return the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to a low heat then add the <strong>chopped spinach </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and cook for 1 min or until the spinach has slightly wilted – this is your <strong>saag sweet potato rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720446803389-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720446803389-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720446803389-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720446803389-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720446803389-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>saag sweet potato rice</strong> and top with the<strong> mango chicken skewers </strong>and<strong> </strong>a dollop of<strong> coriander yoghurt</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
